### High-level description
While upgrading vtk.js from version 12.x to version 24.19.1 we now got a WebGL warning when hiding a viewer

### Steps to reproduce
Create a page with multiple renderers. Dynamically hide or a renderer hidden on page loading will trigger the warning. We using this function to instantiate all of our renderers:
```javascript
    instantiateVtkFullScreenRenderWindow(background)
    {
        const rootContainer = document.getElementById(this.id);

        const renderer = vtkFullScreenRenderWindow.newInstance( {
            rootContainer,
            background: background, //[0.975, 0.975, 0.975]
            containerStyle: {
                overflow: 'hidden',
                height: this.settings.height,
                width: this.settings.width,
            },
        });

        renderer.getRenderer().getActiveCamera().setParallelProjection(true);
        renderer.getRenderer().getActiveCamera().setClippingRange([0.001, 200000]);
        renderer.getRenderer().setLayer(0);

        return renderer;
    }
```

### Detailed behavior

Behavior while hiding a renderer on Chrome
https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/118812869/203296258-4fea0ac4-06e0-4d06-a667-cdec06721e4f.mp4
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/118812869/203296434-a4b1ea29-f029-46cb-8cb7-0fcfb3849fa3.png)

Same issue happens on FF
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/118812869/203296642-abfa9831-eced-4b5d-af10-bb478d97c0b0.png)



### Expected behavior
A hidden renderer should not trigger a WebGL warning

### Environment
- **vtk.js**: 24.19.1
- **OS**:  Windows 10
- **Browser**: Chrome Version 107.0.5304.107 & FF 107.0

